Warning: The Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation Northeast Regional Laboratory (Tahlequah, Oklahoma) received 100 tablets of suspected MDMA. The tablets were of various cartoon shapes including: Autobot, Decepticon, Bart and Homer Simpson, Ninja Turtle, and Smurf (see Photo16). There were also some tablets shaped like Barack Obama and Snoopy. Analysis of the tablets by GC/FID and GC/MS confirmed BZP, TFMPP, and caffeine. No quantitative analysis was performed. This is the second submission of BZP to the laboratory.
